This is a time for caring and healing as we reflect on the kind of nation we want to be.

We face a devastating time as a nation where violence is all too common. While we may never be able to fully eradicate the evil that is in this world, we can each join the fight against a culture of violence in our communities, in our country, and in the world.
I thank the brave members of law enforcement who swiftly responded to these tragedies.

I join Americans across the country, and here in Ohio, in mourning the lives lost at the hands of unspeakable evil. I pray that God will help us all heal, especially those who are directly affected by these tragedies.
